
why these  are deprecated

stop():    terminates thread abruptly,No lock release,no cleanup happens
suspend() :put thread on hold temporarily.No lock is released too.
resume(): used to resume the execution of suspended thread

this lead to deadlock


Join() ========>
when JOIN methods is invoked on a thread object,
current thread will be blocked and waits for the specific
thread to finish

It is helpful when we want to coordinate between threads or
to ensure we complete certain task
before moving ahead